# ğŸ”Ÿ HTML LISTS

HTML lists are used to **group related content**.

### ğŸ”¹ Ordered List `<ol>`

Used when **order matters**.

```html
<ol>
  <li>Login</li>
  <li>Select Course</li>
  <li>Make Payment</li>
</ol>
```

ğŸ“Œ *Real-world:* Step-by-step instructions, rankings.

---

### ğŸ”¹ Unordered List `<ul>`

Used when **order does NOT matter**.

```html
<ul>
  <li>Python</li>
  <li>JavaScript</li>
  <li>HTML</li>
</ul>
```

ğŸ“Œ *Real-world:* Menus, features list.

---

### ğŸ”¹ Description List `<dl>`

Used for **term + explanation**.

```html
<dl>
  <dt>HTML</dt>
  <dd>Structure of webpage</dd>
</dl>
```

ğŸ“Œ *Interview tip:* `<dl>` is semantic, improves SEO.

